      <p></p>
<p>Losing a friend is incredibly painful. These messages seek to acknowledge that pain and offer solace and understanding. Choose words that reflect the nature of your friendship and the specific circumstances of the loss.</p>
<li>I was so saddened to hear about the loss of your friend. My heart goes out to you.</li>
<li>Thinking of you during this difficult time.  May you find peace and comfort.</li>
<li>I'm so sorry for your loss. Your friend will be deeply missed.</li>
<li>Sending you my love and support as you grieve the loss of your dear friend.</li>
<li>Know that I'm here for you, whatever you may need.</li>
<li>My deepest sympathies on the passing of your beloved friend.</li>
<li>I'll always remember [friend's name]'s [positive quality].</li>
<li>Your friendship meant so much to [friend's name].</li>
<li>Please accept my heartfelt condolences on the loss of your friend.</li>
<li>Remembering your friend with warmth and fondness.</li>
<li>I’m so sorry for your loss and sending you strength.</li>
<li>Wishing you peace and comfort as you remember your friend.</li>
